body:
@ackermag found today that she cannot preprocess a study that had a RawData with a single lane because the PrepTemplate was missing the run_prefix.

There was a bug in the way the constraints was checked, as it was assuming that only the forward reads and the barcodes where added. If the reverse reads were added, the test fail and asked for the run_prefix.

This PR fix that problem. This is blocking the processing of current studies so having this merged and deployed is really urgent. @antgonza @ElDeveloper @squirrelo can I have a fast review of this?

…Also adding a test for metadata_headers

@wasade noticed that there was still a couple of references to the `required_sample_info` and `common_prep_info` tables. I'm removing any reference to those here.

The function in which `required_sample_info` was used did not had a test. When I added a test, I noticed that the populate_test_db.sql was not consistent which what our code represents (i.e. we are not allowing to have uppercase column names) so I modified it to be consistent with the rest of our code.

Taking a look to the filepath table in the live system, you can see that the files generated by the meta-analysis pipeline (mapping file and biom file) are still added to the database using the absolute filepath.\

@squirrelo assigning to you since you're the one who is more familiar with that piece of code.

I would say that you'll need a (data) patch to fix this.
